This button allows you to create
variables with a generic name (VAR0001)
and predetermined by the system properties.
*Currently the behavior to create new variables in PSPP differs from that used in SPSS.
For example, in PSPP vast with select box column (name) and automatically creates a variable. In contrast,
in SPSS the variable is created only when a user establishes a name of variable and then type enter.
The PSPP behavior could be the same used in SPSS and automate the process with the proposed new button.
Note: In SPSS, only in instances of creating a variable from its properties or copying and pasting existing variable
is when you set a variable generic name.
In current versions of SPSS, we have added a new column
variable properties.
This new column called "role", can certain options have
predetermined variables with certain options for some types
of analysis, which facilitates the selection and treatment.
These options are: "input", "target", "both", "partition", "segmentation".
These options only affect dialogs selections supporting roles,
and have no effect on other type of test or procedure syntax.
